            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Here's a more practical example. Say I'm a colorscheme plugin developer, and I want to hook into other plugins if they exist. So I have a check like this:\n\n```lua\nlocal success, plugin = pcall(require, 'otherplugin')\nif success then\n  plugin.config {\n    theme = my_colorscheme,\n  }\nend\n```\n\nIf a user installs my colorscheme plugin but doesn't install `otherplugin`, then opening Nvim in a directory containing a `otherplugin.lua` file will run arbitrary code on their machine, with no input required from the user.",
