            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yes, the point of having a lua execution engine is to, in fact, execute lua files on the user's computer.\n\nThis behavior has been fine when used in standalone lua, python, cmd.exe and many many other scripting languages for **multiple decades**.\n\nBut if anyone are really concerned, the issue about default `package.path` could be reported to the Pontifical Catholic University of Rio where lua is developed. ",
